                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.51632 National City Bank/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-03-10T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 10, 1930—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. Your 7 and 8, March 4, 5 p.m. and March 6, 10 a.m. Please discuss freely with
                    Mr. Hart, Vice President National City Bank, your conclusions as to the guilt or
                    innocence of the bank. Bank now requests that you concentrate on obtaining
                    permission for them to put up an individual guarantee rather than cash and the
                    bank relinquishes its request for a postponement of the time limit when the
                    guarantee must be made. Cable present situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
